# Get all permutations of numbers
    perms = list(itertools.permutations(numbers))

    # Initialize an empty list to store the sums of absolute differences for each permutation
    sums = []
    for perm in perms:
        # Shuffle the current permutation
        shuffle(perm)
        # Calculate the sum of absolute differences between each pair of consecutive numbers in the permutation
        sum_diffs = sum([abs(perm[i] - perm[i+1]) for i in range(len(perm)-1)])
        # Append the sum to the sums list
        sums.append(sum_diffs)

    # Calculate the average of the sums and return it
    return sum(sums) / len(sums)

    permutations = itertools.permutations(numbers)

    # Creating a list to store the sums of absolute differences for each permutation
    sums = []

    # Looping through each permutation and adding the sum of absolute differences to the sums list
    for permutation in permutations:
        # Shuffling the permutation randomly
        permutation_list = list(permutation)
        shuffle(permutation_list)

        # Creating a list of absolute differences between consecutive numbers in the permutation
        diffs = [abs(perm[i+1]-perm[i]) for i, perm in enumerate(permutation_list[:-1])]

        # Adding the sum of the differences to the sums list
        sums.append(sum(diffs))

    # Calculating the average of the sums using the mean function
    return sum(sums)/len(sums)
